00:08:26.739 --> 00:08:30.218 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:08:30.218 --> 00:08:35.760 align:middle line:90%


00:08:35.760 --> 00:08:39.539 align:middle line:84%
I believe that we emerge from
the infinite into the finite,

00:08:39.539 --> 00:08:42.159 align:middle line:84%
and it's different
experiences for each of us

00:08:42.159 --> 00:08:44.970 align:middle line:90%
as we make that transition.

00:08:44.970 --> 00:08:49.380 align:middle line:84%
Research clearly shows that one
of the first senses to emerge

00:08:49.380 --> 00:08:51.100 align:middle line:90%
is the sense of hearing.

00:08:51.100 --> 00:08:53.050 align:middle line:84%
When we're little
fetuses developing,

00:08:53.050 --> 00:08:57.170 align:middle line:84%
we are hearing the world
through the liquid medium

00:08:57.170 --> 00:08:59.550 align:middle line:90%
of our mother's womb.

00:08:59.550 --> 00:09:03.010 align:middle line:84%
For me, I was a
forceps delivery,

00:09:03.010 --> 00:09:06.010 align:middle line:84%
so my first experience
of life in this planet

00:09:06.010 --> 00:09:09.130 align:middle line:84%
was something grabbing my
head and pulling me out,

00:09:09.130 --> 00:09:13.060 align:middle line:84%
so I was in a kind of shock,
and I think that shock extended

00:09:13.060 --> 00:09:17.260 align:middle line:84%
past my birth to my early years,
and think this picture of me

00:09:17.260 --> 00:09:21.550 align:middle line:84%
with Santa Claus captures the
essence of my early experience

00:09:21.550 --> 00:09:23.020 align:middle line:90%
in life.

00:09:23.020 --> 00:09:23.920 align:middle line:90%
I mean, can't you just see?

00:09:23.920 --> 00:09:28.360 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, oh my god, where am I?

00:09:28.360 --> 00:09:31.440 align:middle line:84%
I would say my earliest
experience is swinging

00:09:31.440 --> 00:09:35.890 align:middle line:84%
on a swing that my dad made for
me from a limb of an oak tree,

00:09:35.890 --> 00:09:38.190 align:middle line:84%
and I would stay out
there for hours, singing.

00:09:38.190 --> 00:09:40.650 align:middle line:84%
And I would sing to the sun,
and the sun would hear me,

00:09:40.650 --> 00:09:41.730 align:middle line:90%
and I would sing to the moon.

00:09:41.730 --> 00:09:43.620 align:middle line:84%
I would love to stay
up when it got dark,

00:09:43.620 --> 00:09:45.200 align:middle line:84%
and I would sing to
the moon and the stars,

00:09:45.200 --> 00:09:46.920 align:middle line:90%
and I knew they could hear me.

00:09:46.920 --> 00:09:50.020 align:middle line:10%
So I lived in a
world where I could

00:09:50.020 --> 00:09:54.905 align:middle line:10%
sing to beings and celestial
objects, and they responded.

00:09:54.905 --> 00:09:56.680 align:middle line:90%


00:09:56.680 --> 00:09:59.200 align:middle line:90%
[SOUND OF CAR STARTING]

00:09:59.200 --> 00:10:02.560 align:middle line:84%
When I was 12 years-old, our
family had a financial crisis,

00:10:02.560 --> 00:10:05.930 align:middle line:84%
so we had to move into a teeny
tiny efficiency apartment

00:10:05.930 --> 00:10:08.950 align:middle line:84%
by the ocean in the winter,
because rents are really cheap.

00:10:08.950 --> 00:10:11.320 align:middle line:84%
And there was a rec
room underneath that

00:10:11.320 --> 00:10:12.600 align:middle line:90%
had great acoustics.

00:10:12.600 --> 00:10:15.740 align:middle line:84%
It would make, like,
echoes, and I love echoes.

00:10:15.740 --> 00:10:17.270 align:middle line:84%
And so I would go
down there and sing,

00:10:17.270 --> 00:10:18.630 align:middle line:90%
and would travel on the sound.

00:10:18.630 --> 00:10:20.520 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know what I was
doing at 12 years-old,

00:10:20.520 --> 00:10:23.305 align:middle line:84%
but I would just be lost
there for a long, long period

00:10:23.305 --> 00:10:24.005 align:middle line:90%
of time.

00:10:24.005 --> 00:10:27.580 align:middle line:90%


00:10:27.580 --> 00:10:30.720 align:middle line:84%
And one day, the door opened and
a man stepped in that I'd never

00:10:30.720 --> 00:10:32.840 align:middle line:84%
seen before in the
complex, and he said,

00:10:32.840 --> 00:10:34.960 align:middle line:84%
I don't mean to
startle you, but I

00:10:34.960 --> 00:10:37.200 align:middle line:84%
came to tell you that you're
going to heal many people

00:10:37.200 --> 00:10:38.610 align:middle line:90%
in this world with that voice.

00:10:38.610 --> 00:10:40.840 align:middle line:84%
And then he turned and left,
and I never saw him again.

00:10:40.840 --> 00:10:55.820 align:middle line:90%


00:10:55.820 --> 00:10:58.800 align:middle line:84%
This is [INAUDIBLE]
and [INAUDIBLE].

00:10:58.800 --> 00:11:00.690 align:middle line:90%
They're Bodhisattva figures.

00:11:00.690 --> 00:11:02.620 align:middle line:84%
They're from our
love of Thailand,

00:11:02.620 --> 00:11:05.895 align:middle line:84%
and so they guard the passage
with amusing compassion.

00:11:05.895 --> 00:11:08.690 align:middle line:90%


00:11:08.690 --> 00:11:11.196 align:middle line:90%
And to Kuan Yin.

00:11:11.196 --> 00:11:15.590 align:middle line:84%
Kuan Yin is the one who hears
the suffering of the world.

00:11:15.590 --> 00:11:19.731 align:middle line:84%
Sacred to the Taoist and
also to the Buddhist.

00:11:19.731 --> 00:11:24.170 align:middle line:84%
And then over here, we
have the sacred frog.

00:11:24.170 --> 00:11:26.920 align:middle line:90%
The king of the frogs.

00:11:26.920 --> 00:11:30.260 align:middle line:84%
He's an amphibian, so
he goes under water

00:11:30.260 --> 00:11:31.650 align:middle line:84%
into the depths of
the unconscious,

00:11:31.650 --> 00:11:33.920 align:middle line:84%
and he can also
come to the surface.

00:11:33.920 --> 00:11:37.770 align:middle line:84%
And we have the two frogs
making out up on the hill.

00:11:37.770 --> 00:11:40.690 align:middle line:84%
And then we have the
creature of the woods.

00:11:40.690 --> 00:11:42.190 align:middle line:90%
He's the guardian.

00:11:42.190 --> 00:11:44.800 align:middle line:90%
He's like a Druid figure.

00:11:44.800 --> 00:11:46.320 align:middle line:84%
And this is one
of my favorites--

00:11:46.320 --> 00:11:48.630 align:middle line:90%
Our Lady of Guadalupe.

00:11:48.630 --> 00:11:50.300 align:middle line:90%
Beautiful, beautiful being.

00:11:50.300 --> 00:11:53.350 align:middle line:84%
And up here we have a
figure that's hiding.

00:11:53.350 --> 00:11:54.585 align:middle line:90%
This is a Ganesh.

00:11:54.585 --> 00:11:57.470 align:middle line:84%
He's the son of
Shiva and Parvati,

00:11:57.470 --> 00:12:01.426 align:middle line:84%
so represents the part of us
that can overcome obstacles.

00:12:01.426 --> 00:12:04.190 align:middle line:90%
Our two gargoyles.

00:12:04.190 --> 00:12:08.320 align:middle line:84%
This one watches
people who come in.

00:12:08.320 --> 00:12:09.530 align:middle line:90%
This one is still sulking.

00:12:09.530 --> 00:12:11.810 align:middle line:84%
He's just-- he's been
that way since we got him,

00:12:11.810 --> 00:12:13.882 align:middle line:90%
but we love him anyways.

00:12:13.882 --> 00:12:18.790 align:middle line:84%
And then we got this for
Halloween several years ago,

00:12:18.790 --> 00:12:20.750 align:middle line:90%
and just left it up.

00:12:20.750 --> 00:12:22.395 align:middle line:90%
And I kind of like it.

00:12:22.395 --> 00:12:23.335 align:middle line:90%
It's just a reminder.

00:12:23.335 --> 00:12:27.209 align:middle line:90%


00:12:27.209 --> 00:12:28.203 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12:28.203 --> 00:12:37.149 align:middle line:84%
(SINGING) The Countess of your
heart, yes, and the [INAUDIBLE]

00:12:37.149 --> 00:12:47.610 align:middle line:84%
waits for you by
the stream to carry

00:12:47.610 --> 00:12:52.695 align:middle line:90%
you into the land of dreams.

00:12:52.695 --> 00:12:58.515 align:middle line:90%


00:12:58.515 --> 00:13:00.950 align:middle line:10%
[BIG  BAND MUSIC PLAYING]

00:13:00.950 --> 00:13:03.570 align:middle line:10%
Well, my mother was a
professional singer,

00:13:03.570 --> 00:13:05.285 align:middle line:10%
so that's where, actually,
my voice came from.

00:13:05.285 --> 00:13:08.500 align:middle line:84%
And she sang with the
big bands in the 1940s.

00:13:08.500 --> 00:13:11.945 align:middle line:84%
She was actually a
circus elephant rider,

00:13:11.945 --> 00:13:14.930 align:middle line:84%
and in those days, the
circus would come into town,

00:13:14.930 --> 00:13:18.490 align:middle line:84%
and she was the one who rode
the elephant for that circus.

00:13:18.490 --> 00:13:22.030 align:middle line:84%
And then when the show
began, in between the acts,

00:13:22.030 --> 00:13:23.640 align:middle line:84%
the big band would
play, and she'd sing.

00:13:23.640 --> 00:13:26.180 align:middle line:90%
So she was always singing.

00:13:26.180 --> 00:13:30.170 align:middle line:84%
And I just started singing
in church, in choirs,

00:13:30.170 --> 00:13:36.040 align:middle line:84%
and then a crucial period came
when I individuated from my mom

00:13:36.040 --> 00:13:37.890 align:middle line:90%
and decided to get a guitar.

00:13:37.890 --> 00:13:40.100 align:middle line:84%
And for her, that was
a evil instrument,

00:13:40.100 --> 00:13:44.450 align:middle line:84%
because in the bands, the people
that she saw playing guitar

00:13:44.450 --> 00:13:45.990 align:middle line:90%
were drug addicts.

00:13:45.990 --> 00:13:48.400 align:middle line:84%
So she thought that if
I picked up the guitar,

00:13:48.400 --> 00:13:49.980 align:middle line:90%
I would become a drug addict.

00:13:49.980 --> 00:13:51.720 align:middle line:84%
And of course, this was
the time of folk music,

00:13:51.720 --> 00:13:53.760 align:middle line:84%
and that was really
what I was moving into,

00:13:53.760 --> 00:13:55.280 align:middle line:84%
so I had to save up
my money, because she

00:13:55.280 --> 00:13:56.500 align:middle line:90%
refused to buy me a guitar.

00:13:56.500 --> 00:13:57.290 align:middle line:84%
She said, if you're
going to have a guitar,

00:13:57.290 --> 00:13:58.123 align:middle line:90%
you must get it yourself.

00:13:58.123 --> 00:14:01.120 align:middle line:84%
One night I went into
a lounge, and they

00:14:01.120 --> 00:14:02.930 align:middle line:84%
had, like, amateur
night or something,

00:14:02.930 --> 00:14:04.490 align:middle line:84%
and I played, and
they offered me a job,

00:14:04.490 --> 00:14:06.650 align:middle line:90%
so I became a lounge singer.

00:14:06.650 --> 00:14:08.940 align:middle line:84%
So I would play
guitar and piano.

00:14:08.940 --> 00:14:11.370 align:middle line:84%
So I performed at the place
underneath the Chinese

00:14:11.370 --> 00:14:15.800 align:middle line:84%
restaurant, and two friends
of mine-- Marty and Kim--

00:14:15.800 --> 00:14:16.600 align:middle line:90%
helped run it.

00:14:16.600 --> 00:14:19.610 align:middle line:84%
And I think he was hanging
sheet rock at the time,

00:14:19.610 --> 00:14:23.800 align:middle line:84%
and went into this story about
how his landlady was kicking

00:14:23.800 --> 00:14:27.670 align:middle line:84%
him out, and then he sang,
Can't Find My Way Home,

00:14:27.670 --> 00:14:31.610 align:middle line:84%
and so I went up to
Marty, I said, this guy

00:14:31.610 --> 00:14:33.560 align:middle line:90%
doesn't have any place to live.

00:14:33.560 --> 00:14:36.210 align:middle line:84%
Let's ask him to live with
us, and we did that night.

00:14:36.210 --> 00:14:36.950 align:middle line:90%
We did.

00:14:36.950 --> 00:14:39.641 align:middle line:84%
And he came and he
lived with us for about--

00:14:39.641 --> 00:14:40.340 align:middle line:90%
A couple--

00:14:40.340 --> 00:14:41.440 align:middle line:84%
 --a year and a
half, two years.

00:14:41.440 --> 00:14:42.960 align:middle line:10%
Yeah, year and and
a half, or two years.

00:14:42.960 --> 00:14:45.660 align:middle line:10%
He was writing a lot
of music at that point,

00:14:45.660 --> 00:14:52.960 align:middle line:10%
and he really was hoping that
he would make it as a singer.

00:14:52.960 --> 00:14:57.770 align:middle line:84%
I was really into pop rock,
but I didn't have the resources

00:14:57.770 --> 00:14:59.010 align:middle line:90%
to get to Los Angeles.

00:14:59.010 --> 00:15:02.560 align:middle line:84%
I lived in North Carolina,
so Nashville was closer.

00:15:02.560 --> 00:15:04.970 align:middle line:84%
So I started writing
country songs.

00:15:04.970 --> 00:15:07.980 align:middle line:84%
And I went to Nashville,
and worked in restaurants,

00:15:07.980 --> 00:15:11.200 align:middle line:90%
and gigs-- music gigs.

00:15:11.200 --> 00:15:16.000 align:middle line:84%
And the really weird thing was
that the record engineer guys--

00:15:16.000 --> 00:15:18.030 align:middle line:84%
I would go in for sessions,
and they would say,

00:15:18.030 --> 00:15:18.985 align:middle line:90%
you're really, really good.

00:15:18.985 --> 00:15:19.950 align:middle line:90%
You're really talented.

00:15:19.950 --> 00:15:22.295 align:middle line:84%
Just wait-- somebody's
going to pick you up.

00:15:22.295 --> 00:15:27.280 align:middle line:90%


00:15:27.280 --> 00:15:30.360 align:middle line:84%
It was autumn--
early autumn-- and I

00:15:30.360 --> 00:15:32.680 align:middle line:84%
was walking across a cow
pasture of my uncle's

00:15:32.680 --> 00:15:33.860 align:middle line:90%
farm in North Carolina.

00:15:33.860 --> 00:15:38.190 align:middle line:84%
And I sat underneath a
tree, I folded my legs

00:15:38.190 --> 00:15:41.120 align:middle line:84%
in like a half Lotus-- I didn't
even know what I was doing--

00:15:41.120 --> 00:15:43.200 align:middle line:84%
and then my hands
went spontaneously

00:15:43.200 --> 00:15:45.060 align:middle line:90%
into these mudras.

00:15:45.060 --> 00:15:48.880 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sitting there
underneath the tree like a Yogi

00:15:48.880 --> 00:15:53.960 align:middle line:84%
from Muskogee, and my hands
are doing these weird mudras.

00:15:53.960 --> 00:15:57.450 align:middle line:84%
I went into a deep place
and the world disappeared.

00:15:57.450 --> 00:15:59.190 align:middle line:84%
I had no sensory
experience of the world.

00:15:59.190 --> 00:16:02.370 align:middle line:84%
I thought it lasted
for a few moments,

00:16:02.370 --> 00:16:05.220 align:middle line:84%
but when I opened my
eyes, the sun was setting,

00:16:05.220 --> 00:16:07.270 align:middle line:90%
so several hours had passed.

00:16:07.270 --> 00:16:09.620 align:middle line:84%
And several cows
had wandered over

00:16:09.620 --> 00:16:12.630 align:middle line:84%
and were staring at me,
when I opened my eyes.

00:16:12.630 --> 00:16:17.420 align:middle line:10%
For whatever reason, a white boy
is walking across a cow pasture

00:16:17.420 --> 00:16:18.935 align:middle line:10%
one autumn afternoon,
and goes into

00:16:18.935 --> 00:16:23.610 align:middle line:10%
a spontaneous yogic samadhi,
and experiences Sat Chit Ananda.

00:16:23.610 --> 00:16:26.410 align:middle line:10%
And the impact of
that was so profound

00:16:26.410 --> 00:16:29.520 align:middle line:10%
that for hours afterwards I
was in love with the world.

00:16:29.520 --> 00:16:31.340 align:middle line:84%
I could feel the
love of everything,

00:16:31.340 --> 00:16:35.150 align:middle line:84%
and I was a deep place
of contentment and peace.

00:16:35.150 --> 00:16:38.900 align:middle line:84%
I didn't even know what samadhi
was or what [INAUDIBLE] were,

00:16:38.900 --> 00:16:42.260 align:middle line:84%
and so I started to search
for what the meaning

00:16:42.260 --> 00:16:43.075 align:middle line:90%
was of that experience.

00:16:43.075 --> 00:16:48.320 align:middle line:90%


00:16:48.320 --> 00:16:50.440 align:middle line:84%
I started researching
and studying,

00:16:50.440 --> 00:16:53.080 align:middle line:84%
and discovered the
mystic contemplatives

00:16:53.080 --> 00:16:54.220 align:middle line:90%
of the Middle Ages.

00:16:54.220 --> 00:16:58.170 align:middle line:10%
They were describing something
of what I had experienced,

00:16:58.170 --> 00:17:01.160 align:middle line:10%
but with not the
complete picture.

00:17:01.160 --> 00:17:05.220 align:middle line:10%
But one of the roots of
that spiritual tradition

00:17:05.220 --> 00:17:07.920 align:middle line:10%
is contemplative, and
is an inner journey,

00:17:07.920 --> 00:17:09.900 align:middle line:10%
and that's what I
became interested in.

00:17:09.900 --> 00:17:12.837 align:middle line:84%
So I went to a Catholic
college for two years,

00:17:12.837 --> 00:17:13.970 align:middle line:84%
because I thought
that I was going

00:17:13.970 --> 00:17:16.069 align:middle line:90%
to become a Trappist monk.

00:17:16.069 --> 00:17:19.160 align:middle line:84%
And I was drawn to the Trappists
because they're a silent order,

00:17:19.160 --> 00:17:20.690 align:middle line:84%
which would be ironic
if I had become

00:17:20.690 --> 00:17:24.040 align:middle line:84%
a Trappist, with a voice,
and I would become silent.

00:17:24.040 --> 00:17:25.971 align:middle line:90%


00:17:25.971 --> 00:17:26.670 align:middle line:90%
Shhh.

00:17:26.670 --> 00:17:31.450 align:middle line:84%
TOM KENYON: I went to the mass,
and I was mesmerized, and fell

00:17:31.450 --> 00:17:33.540 align:middle line:84%
in love with the
mass-- with the Latin,

00:17:33.540 --> 00:17:38.900 align:middle line:84%
and the incense, and the
gold, and the pageantry,

00:17:38.900 --> 00:17:41.300 align:middle line:90%
the stained glass.

00:17:41.300 --> 00:17:44.010 align:middle line:84%
And then it just so happened
that they did the mass

00:17:44.010 --> 00:17:46.240 align:middle line:84%
in English, and
for the first time,

00:17:46.240 --> 00:17:49.002 align:middle line:84%
I heard what they
were actually saying.

00:17:49.002 --> 00:17:53.580 align:middle line:84%
And I could not
accept that reality,

00:17:53.580 --> 00:17:56.270 align:middle line:90%
because it was guilt and shame.

00:17:56.270 --> 00:17:57.430 align:middle line:90%
Guilt and shame.

00:17:57.430 --> 00:17:59.940 align:middle line:84%
Mea culpa, mea culpa,
mea maxima culpa.

00:17:59.940 --> 00:18:02.210 align:middle line:84%
I just couldn't accept
that, because when

00:18:02.210 --> 00:18:04.030 align:middle line:84%
I went into these
mystical experiences

00:18:04.030 --> 00:18:06.850 align:middle line:84%
and I was with St. Teresa,
or I was with St. Francis,

00:18:06.850 --> 00:18:10.040 align:middle line:84%
or I was with Mary-- I had a
lot of experiences with Mary,

00:18:10.040 --> 00:18:12.960 align:middle line:84%
the mother-- there
was no shame and there

00:18:12.960 --> 00:18:15.140 align:middle line:90%
was no guilt from any of them.

00:18:15.140 --> 00:18:22.040 align:middle line:84%
It was a pure agape-- pure
love-- without any condition.

00:18:22.040 --> 00:18:25.350 align:middle line:84%
So I was having these mystical
experiences that were typical

00:18:25.350 --> 00:18:29.880 align:middle line:84%
of people in the 13th,
14th, 15th centuries,

00:18:29.880 --> 00:18:34.540 align:middle line:84%
and I'm living in a 20th century
world, and that was a mismatch.

00:18:34.540 --> 00:18:37.460 align:middle line:90%
So I left the church behind.

00:18:37.460 --> 00:18:40.860 align:middle line:90%


00:18:40.860 --> 00:18:43.790 align:middle line:84%
And the quest was about
understanding what

00:18:43.790 --> 00:18:47.320 align:middle line:84%
mystical experiences were,
and bringing the human

00:18:47.320 --> 00:18:49.900 align:middle line:90%
and the divine together.

00:18:49.900 --> 00:18:50.880 align:middle line:90%
Can you bring them together?

00:18:50.880 --> 00:19:02.450 align:middle line:90%


00:19:02.450 --> 00:19:05.430 align:middle line:90%
Sophia means wisdom.

00:19:05.430 --> 00:19:09.390 align:middle line:84%
The Gnostics say that Sophia
is actually the heroine

00:19:09.390 --> 00:19:11.850 align:middle line:90%
and the protector of humanity.

00:19:11.850 --> 00:19:17.591 align:middle line:84%
She's said to be the
feminine counterpart to God.

00:19:17.591 --> 00:19:18.790 align:middle line:84%
-[INAUDIBLE]
-Yes.

00:19:18.790 --> 00:19:19.790 align:middle line:90%
It would.

00:19:19.790 --> 00:19:22.778 align:middle line:90%


00:19:22.778 --> 00:19:29.694 align:middle line:10%
[BELLS RINGING]

00:19:29.694 --> 00:19:34.140 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING AND CHANTING]

00:19:34.140 --> 00:20:33.720 align:middle line:90%


00:20:33.720 --> 00:20:47.315 align:middle line:84%
(SINGING) Sophia,
Sophia, Sophia.

00:20:47.315 --> 00:21:09.150 align:middle line:90%


00:21:09.150 --> 00:21:11.400 align:middle line:10%
I continued my education at the
University of North Carolina,

00:21:11.400 --> 00:21:14.060 align:middle line:10%
Greensboro, minored
in psychology,

00:21:14.060 --> 00:21:20.190 align:middle line:10%
and I was taking a class on
psychosis, which is, basically,

00:21:20.190 --> 00:21:21.674 align:middle line:10%
the mental state
where a person is

00:21:21.674 --> 00:21:23.140 align:middle line:10%
seeing things that
aren't there, and hearing

00:21:23.140 --> 00:21:23.973 align:middle line:10%
things that aren't there.

00:21:23.973 --> 00:21:27.104 align:middle line:90%


00:21:27.104 --> 00:21:28.270 align:middle line:84%
But I remember it
was a spring day,

00:21:28.270 --> 00:21:30.790 align:middle line:84%
and I'm on my way-- I was
on my way to this class,

00:21:30.790 --> 00:21:33.480 align:middle line:84%
and I had read the notes, so I
knew what it was talking about.

00:21:33.480 --> 00:21:35.530 align:middle line:84%
And on either side
of me are two angels,

00:21:35.530 --> 00:21:37.270 align:middle line:90%
suddenly, out of the blue.

00:21:37.270 --> 00:21:39.320 align:middle line:84%
Complete with the
frigging wings.

00:21:39.320 --> 00:21:41.780 align:middle line:84%
They're about nine feet
tall, with white wings--

00:21:41.780 --> 00:21:44.320 align:middle line:84%
brilliant white-- emanating
white light brilliantly.

00:21:44.320 --> 00:21:47.400 align:middle line:84%
Now, I was aware that it was
a mental impression, so it

00:21:47.400 --> 00:21:48.630 align:middle line:90%
was not a true hallucination.

00:21:48.630 --> 00:21:51.620 align:middle line:84%
In other words, I was aware
that it was coming from somehow

00:21:51.620 --> 00:21:55.020 align:middle line:84%
in my mind, but I experienced
them as physically

00:21:55.020 --> 00:21:56.870 align:middle line:90%
real outside of me.

00:21:56.870 --> 00:22:00.820 align:middle line:84%
And so I became
absolutely freaked out,

00:22:00.820 --> 00:22:03.750 align:middle line:84%
like, I'm going to a
class on psychosis,

00:22:03.750 --> 00:22:06.210 align:middle line:84%
and two angels are
walking beside me.

00:22:06.210 --> 00:22:09.600 align:middle line:84%
What if I walk in the
class and nobody sees them?

00:22:09.600 --> 00:22:14.200 align:middle line:84%
Or, worse, what if I walk in the
class and people do see them?

00:22:14.200 --> 00:22:15.690 align:middle line:90%
How do I explain them?

00:22:15.690 --> 00:22:17.410 align:middle line:84%
And what was really
weird in that

00:22:17.410 --> 00:22:20.220 align:middle line:84%
moment was I felt this immense
love coming from them that was

00:22:20.220 --> 00:22:25.780 align:middle line:84%
just, like, melting me, but my
paranoia about who they were,

00:22:25.780 --> 00:22:28.420 align:middle line:84%
and what was this, and are
they real, was so big, I said,

00:22:28.420 --> 00:22:31.200 align:middle line:84%
you guys have to go away, and
they-- poof-- they disappeared.

00:22:31.200 --> 00:22:33.630 align:middle line:90%


00:22:33.630 --> 00:22:36.700 align:middle line:84%
I went into psychology,
looking back at it,

00:22:36.700 --> 00:22:40.740 align:middle line:84%
to discover if
maybe I was crazy.

00:22:40.740 --> 00:22:44.460 align:middle line:84%
And I found among my fellow
students that many of us

00:22:44.460 --> 00:22:49.270 align:middle line:84%
were in the psych
department for that reason.

00:22:49.270 --> 00:22:51.590 align:middle line:84%
I lived in an old
dilapidated house

00:22:51.590 --> 00:22:52.860 align:middle line:90%
that should've been condemned.

00:22:52.860 --> 00:22:55.650 align:middle line:84%
I had a mattress on
one corner of the room,

00:22:55.650 --> 00:22:59.570 align:middle line:84%
and there was half
written papers, and books,

00:22:59.570 --> 00:23:04.120 align:middle line:84%
and laundry, and
food, and dust balls,

00:23:04.120 --> 00:23:05.790 align:middle line:84%
and the whole
thing of a student.

00:23:05.790 --> 00:23:07.240 align:middle line:84%
And on the other
side of the room,

00:23:07.240 --> 00:23:10.160 align:middle line:84%
I had an altar, and pictures
of the saints of all

00:23:10.160 --> 00:23:13.620 align:middle line:84%
the traditions I was
exploring, and a prayer rug,

00:23:13.620 --> 00:23:15.680 align:middle line:90%
and it was pristine.

00:23:15.680 --> 00:23:19.420 align:middle line:84%
And there was this tension
between me as Tom the person

00:23:19.420 --> 00:23:21.910 align:middle line:90%
and Tom the aspiring yogi.

00:23:21.910 --> 00:23:24.820 align:middle line:84%
And so really the quest was, how
do you bring the two together?

00:23:24.820 --> 00:23:28.360 align:middle line:90%


00:23:28.360 --> 00:23:32.780 align:middle line:84%
There were several incidences in
my education at the university

00:23:32.780 --> 00:23:34.990 align:middle line:90%
that were significant for me.

00:23:34.990 --> 00:23:38.920 align:middle line:84%
One of them was the discovery
that your physiology

00:23:38.920 --> 00:23:44.320 align:middle line:84%
could be used as a language to
explain mystical experiences.

00:23:44.320 --> 00:23:47.410 align:middle line:84%
The whole time while I was going
through my scientific training,

00:23:47.410 --> 00:23:50.440 align:middle line:84%
I was going deeper into
the mysticism of the East.

00:23:50.440 --> 00:23:53.950 align:middle line:84%
The yoga of India,
Taosim of China,

00:23:53.950 --> 00:23:57.480 align:middle line:84%
Egyptian alchemy,
Tibetan Buddhism.

00:23:57.480 --> 00:23:59.190 align:middle line:84%
I was practicing
every meditation

00:23:59.190 --> 00:24:01.030 align:middle line:90%
from every tradition.

00:24:01.030 --> 00:24:02.920 align:middle line:84%
I would sometimes
spend five hours a day

00:24:02.920 --> 00:24:04.330 align:middle line:90%
meditating different practices.

00:24:04.330 --> 00:24:08.160 align:middle line:90%


00:24:08.160 --> 00:24:10.900 align:middle line:84%
And so I was changing
my neurophysiology

00:24:10.900 --> 00:24:13.090 align:middle line:90%
and not realizing it.

00:24:13.090 --> 00:24:16.140 align:middle line:84%
So I had been doing Kundalini
practices along with everything

00:24:16.140 --> 00:24:20.710 align:middle line:84%
else, and it was spring, people
were in the quadrangle throwing

00:24:20.710 --> 00:24:24.260 align:middle line:84%
Frisbees, there were
high-rise dorms,

00:24:24.260 --> 00:24:27.100 align:middle line:84%
and I was sitting there just
enjoying everything, and then

00:24:27.100 --> 00:24:28.220 align:middle line:90%
all of a sudden I hear this--

00:24:28.220 --> 00:24:30.090 align:middle line:90%
[RATTLESNAKE SOUND]

00:24:30.090 --> 00:24:33.550 align:middle line:84%
--sound, that goes right
up my spine, like a snake.

00:24:33.550 --> 00:24:36.470 align:middle line:84%
And of course, in
symbolism, Kundalini shakti

00:24:36.470 --> 00:24:39.610 align:middle line:90%
is symbolized as a cobra.

00:24:39.610 --> 00:24:42.175 align:middle line:84%
And that's because, as the
energy rises up the spine, when

00:24:42.175 --> 00:24:46.694 align:middle line:84%
it hits the brain, it spreads
out like the hood of a cobra,

00:24:46.694 --> 00:24:48.760 align:middle line:84%
and what it's doing is actually
going through both hemispheres

00:24:48.760 --> 00:24:49.500 align:middle line:90%
of the brain.

00:24:49.500 --> 00:24:52.320 align:middle line:84%
And this shakti-- this
immense electric charge--

00:24:52.320 --> 00:24:56.110 align:middle line:84%
was going into my brain, and
just lit up all these centers.

00:24:56.110 --> 00:24:59.420 align:middle line:84%
My experience was that the
dorms became transparent.

00:24:59.420 --> 00:25:03.990 align:middle line:84%
I could see through the walls,
and I could feel every emotion

00:25:03.990 --> 00:25:07.410 align:middle line:84%
of all the thousand
or so students that

00:25:07.410 --> 00:25:10.240 align:middle line:84%
were in the area-- their
hopes, their dreams,

00:25:10.240 --> 00:25:14.570 align:middle line:84%
their fears, going into
exams, all that stuff.

00:25:14.570 --> 00:25:17.060 align:middle line:84%
And then I started-- then
I heard the sound again--

00:25:17.060 --> 00:25:18.010 align:middle line:90%
[RATTLESNAKE SOUND]

00:25:18.010 --> 00:25:21.230 align:middle line:84%
--and another surge
went up into my brain,

00:25:21.230 --> 00:25:25.715 align:middle line:84%
and I felt really hot,
like burning up-- it's

00:25:25.715 --> 00:25:29.180 align:middle line:84%
called psychic fire
in the tradition.

00:25:29.180 --> 00:25:31.010 align:middle line:90%
But I didn't know what it was.

00:25:31.010 --> 00:25:33.580 align:middle line:84%
And so I start to
walk back to the dorm,

00:25:33.580 --> 00:25:36.140 align:middle line:84%
and as I'm going
back to the dorm,

00:25:36.140 --> 00:25:39.420 align:middle line:84%
my friends are going to lunch,
and they're walking by me,

00:25:39.420 --> 00:25:41.650 align:middle line:90%
and say, come on with us, Tom.

00:25:41.650 --> 00:25:44.620 align:middle line:84%
And I say, no, I can't, I'm
going to go back and lie down.

00:25:44.620 --> 00:25:47.770 align:middle line:84%
Well, what was weird was, it
was like my perception was

00:25:47.770 --> 00:25:51.480 align:middle line:90%
they were in a different movie.

00:25:51.480 --> 00:25:54.510 align:middle line:84%
I could see the movie, but I
couldn't step into their movie.

00:25:54.510 --> 00:25:56.890 align:middle line:90%
I was another movie.

00:25:56.890 --> 00:25:58.725 align:middle line:90%
So I am hot.

00:25:58.725 --> 00:26:00.320 align:middle line:84%
I'm so hot, I want
to go to the dorm

00:26:00.320 --> 00:26:02.980 align:middle line:84%
and just get a cold shower,
and then I'm getting so weak,

00:26:02.980 --> 00:26:04.570 align:middle line:84%
it's like I have
no energy to move.

00:26:04.570 --> 00:26:07.370 align:middle line:84%
And I look, and it's-- I look
to the right, and that's where

00:26:07.370 --> 00:26:09.550 align:middle line:90%
the student health center is.

00:26:09.550 --> 00:26:14.600 align:middle line:84%
And my dorm is about
another 500 yards away,

00:26:14.600 --> 00:26:17.260 align:middle line:84%
and the student health
center is right here,

00:26:17.260 --> 00:26:19.070 align:middle line:84%
and I feel like I'm--
literally, the life

00:26:19.070 --> 00:26:21.660 align:middle line:90%
force is draining out of me.

00:26:21.660 --> 00:26:25.510 align:middle line:84%
So I walk towards
the health center,

00:26:25.510 --> 00:26:28.730 align:middle line:84%
and literally, the energy
leaves my arms and my hands,

00:26:28.730 --> 00:26:31.730 align:middle line:84%
and I have to crawl in onto
the porch-- I'm crawling in--

00:26:31.730 --> 00:26:33.280 align:middle line:84%
and this is really
bizarre-- I'm crawling

00:26:33.280 --> 00:26:35.050 align:middle line:90%
into the health center.

00:26:35.050 --> 00:26:38.470 align:middle line:84%
And I sit in a chair,
and the nurse comes in,

00:26:38.470 --> 00:26:39.830 align:middle line:90%
and I show her my ID.

00:26:39.830 --> 00:26:42.960 align:middle line:84%
She takes my temperature
and she turns ashen white.

00:26:42.960 --> 00:26:45.010 align:middle line:84%
All I remember is her
eyes got really wide,

00:26:45.010 --> 00:26:47.900 align:middle line:84%
and her color changed,
and she ran off.

00:26:47.900 --> 00:26:51.260 align:middle line:84%
In comes the doctor, and
the next thing I know,

00:26:51.260 --> 00:26:53.480 align:middle line:84%
I'm in a private
room, and they're

00:26:53.480 --> 00:26:56.095 align:middle line:90%
giving me whatever medicine.

00:26:56.095 --> 00:26:57.395 align:middle line:84%
I still, , to this
day, don't know what

00:26:57.395 --> 00:26:58.930 align:middle line:90%
medicines they're giving me.

00:26:58.930 --> 00:27:04.390 align:middle line:84%
Fortunately, I didn't say
anything about a snake going up

00:27:04.390 --> 00:27:08.220 align:middle line:84%
my spine, or seeing through
the walls of the dorms,

00:27:08.220 --> 00:27:09.290 align:middle line:90%
or any of that.

00:27:09.290 --> 00:27:12.180 align:middle line:90%
What I presented was a fever.

00:27:12.180 --> 00:27:14.530 align:middle line:84%
So they put me in
a medical wing,

00:27:14.530 --> 00:27:16.640 align:middle line:90%
not the psychological wing.

00:27:16.640 --> 00:27:19.900 align:middle line:84%
And so for three
days I was delirious.

00:27:19.900 --> 00:27:22.310 align:middle line:84%
Because what my understanding
of what happened

00:27:22.310 --> 00:27:25.250 align:middle line:84%
was, that the Kundalini
had gone into an area

00:27:25.250 --> 00:27:28.890 align:middle line:84%
of my neurophysiology-- subtle
neurophysiology-- the chakra

00:27:28.890 --> 00:27:31.450 align:middle line:84%
system and the
nadis, where there

00:27:31.450 --> 00:27:34.460 align:middle line:84%
were impurities, because I had
not prepared myself properly.

00:27:34.460 --> 00:27:36.730 align:middle line:90%
I had pushed the river.

00:27:36.730 --> 00:27:38.260 align:middle line:84%
And for three days
I was in a state

00:27:38.260 --> 00:27:40.340 align:middle line:90%
of delirium and a high fever.

00:27:40.340 --> 00:27:43.760 align:middle line:84%
And I remember the images
vividly to this day.

00:27:43.760 --> 00:27:45.190 align:middle line:90%
There were two sets of them.

00:27:45.190 --> 00:27:48.675 align:middle line:84%
One was I was on a raft
floating on an ocean--

00:27:48.675 --> 00:27:52.400 align:middle line:84%
a vast ocean with dark
clouds, with sea monsters

00:27:52.400 --> 00:27:54.630 align:middle line:84%
trying to grab me
off of the raft

00:27:54.630 --> 00:27:57.120 align:middle line:84%
and pull me down
into the depths.

00:27:57.120 --> 00:27:59.490 align:middle line:84%
That's classic
Jungian psychology.

00:27:59.490 --> 00:28:01.980 align:middle line:84%
The ocean is the
unconscious, it was stirred,

00:28:01.980 --> 00:28:04.990 align:middle line:90%
and emotions, and all of that.

00:28:04.990 --> 00:28:08.980 align:middle line:90%
And this went on for three days.

00:28:08.980 --> 00:28:12.130 align:middle line:84%
And then the other vision was, I
would be driving along a desert

00:28:12.130 --> 00:28:16.380 align:middle line:84%
in my grandfather's
Ford, and I would

00:28:16.380 --> 00:28:20.370 align:middle line:84%
see the sunset in the hub of
the wheel-- the steering wheel.

00:28:20.370 --> 00:28:23.520 align:middle line:84%
And off in the distance
was a little, like,

00:28:23.520 --> 00:28:27.730 align:middle line:84%
an adobe in the desert, and
I knew that in that house

00:28:27.730 --> 00:28:31.330 align:middle line:84%
was somebody who knew the
secret of the universe.

00:28:31.330 --> 00:28:34.360 align:middle line:84%
And as I got closer,
it would hop away,

00:28:34.360 --> 00:28:36.500 align:middle line:90%
and I could never get to it.

00:28:36.500 --> 00:28:38.750 align:middle line:84%
And then I came out
of the delirium,

00:28:38.750 --> 00:28:40.440 align:middle line:84%
and I was weak for
about six weeks,

00:28:40.440 --> 00:28:44.050 align:middle line:84%
to regain my strength,
from a premature experience

00:28:44.050 --> 00:28:45.390 align:middle line:90%
with Kundalini shakti.

00:28:45.390 --> 00:28:50.422 align:middle line:84%
So I became very respectful
of this primordial power.

00:28:50.422 --> 00:28:54.310 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING AND SINGING]

00:28:54.310 --> 00:31:17.010 align:middle line:90%


00:31:17.010 --> 00:31:21.700 align:middle line:84%
Sound vibrations speaks to our
souls, it speaks to our bodies,

00:31:21.700 --> 00:31:25.710 align:middle line:84%
it bypasses the cognitive
mind, and when that happens,

00:31:25.710 --> 00:31:30.030 align:middle line:84%
a door opens, and people
can go through that door,

00:31:30.030 --> 00:31:32.755 align:middle line:84%
and discover miracles and
mysteries in themselves

00:31:32.755 --> 00:31:34.210 align:middle line:90%
that they never imagined.

00:31:34.210 --> 00:31:41.360 align:middle line:90%


00:31:41.360 --> 00:31:43.190 align:middle line:84%
So after my
undergraduate degree,

00:31:43.190 --> 00:31:46.570 align:middle line:84%
I went to California to study
something called whole brain

00:31:46.570 --> 00:31:49.230 align:middle line:84%
learning, which is
a method for using

00:31:49.230 --> 00:31:52.620 align:middle line:84%
music, sound, and
frequency to open up

00:31:52.620 --> 00:31:54.570 align:middle line:90%
latent potentials of the brain.

00:31:54.570 --> 00:31:57.080 align:middle line:84%
And so I had this body
of knowledge about sound

00:31:57.080 --> 00:31:59.970 align:middle line:84%
and how it could affect altered
states of consciousness,

00:31:59.970 --> 00:32:02.970 align:middle line:84%
and psychological
counseling, and

00:32:02.970 --> 00:32:04.980 align:middle line:90%
different psychological states.

00:32:04.980 --> 00:32:09.170 align:middle line:84%
And the challenge, for me, was
to bring those two together.

00:32:09.170 --> 00:32:12.430 align:middle line:84%
And I discovered the work
of Losanov of Bulgaria--

00:32:12.430 --> 00:32:13.730 align:middle line:90%
the Losanov Institute.

00:32:13.730 --> 00:32:18.560 align:middle line:10%
And he was documenting how music
could increase alpha activity,

00:32:18.560 --> 00:32:22.660 align:middle line:10%
which is a precursor to the
lower brain activity of theta,

00:32:22.660 --> 00:32:24.391 align:middle line:10%
and this is the range
of hypnotic states

00:32:24.391 --> 00:32:25.090 align:middle line:10%
of consciousness.

00:32:25.090 --> 00:32:27.190 align:middle line:10%
So as a therapist
I was fascinated,

00:32:27.190 --> 00:32:28.331 align:middle line:10%
and also being a musician.

00:32:28.331 --> 00:32:29.664 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC - JOHANNES BRAHMS "CRADLE
 SONG"]

00:32:29.664 --> 00:32:32.420 align:middle line:90%


00:32:32.420 --> 00:32:34.850 align:middle line:84%
And there was a study done
with premature babies,

00:32:34.850 --> 00:32:38.460 align:middle line:84%
and Brahms' Lullaby was
played to a control group,

00:32:38.460 --> 00:32:42.150 align:middle line:84%
and Brahms' Lullaby was not
played to another group.

00:32:42.150 --> 00:32:45.190 align:middle line:84%
And what happened with the
Brahms' babies was that they

00:32:45.190 --> 00:32:47.990 align:middle line:84%
were released from the hospital
an average of a week earlier,

00:32:47.990 --> 00:32:51.430 align:middle line:84%
had fewer complications,
and thrived

00:32:51.430 --> 00:32:52.740 align:middle line:90%
better than the other babies.

00:32:52.740 --> 00:32:54.460 align:middle line:90%


00:32:54.460 --> 00:32:57.930 align:middle line:84%
And what it turns out to be is
that the structure of the music

00:32:57.930 --> 00:33:00.610 align:middle line:84%
of Brahms-- these
particular pieces-- soothed

00:33:00.610 --> 00:33:02.750 align:middle line:84%
the nervous system,
increased alpha activity,

00:33:02.750 --> 00:33:05.440 align:middle line:84%
and again, when you have an
increase of alpha activities,

00:33:05.440 --> 00:33:08.170 align:middle line:84%
there's a decrease of
blood pressure, heart rate,

00:33:08.170 --> 00:33:11.690 align:middle line:90%
respiration, stress hormones.

00:33:11.690 --> 00:33:14.660 align:middle line:84%
And the sound, the music, the
structure, the architecture,

00:33:14.660 --> 00:33:17.260 align:middle line:84%
the tambor-- the sound
quality of the instruments--

00:33:17.260 --> 00:33:20.310 align:middle line:84%
the rhythm, very
importantly, and the melody

00:33:20.310 --> 00:33:22.790 align:middle line:84%
soothed the brain and
created this increase

00:33:22.790 --> 00:33:24.430 align:middle line:90%
of alpha response.

00:33:24.430 --> 00:33:28.957 align:middle line:84%
So the babies were having an
opportunity for self-healing,

00:33:28.957 --> 00:33:30.190 align:middle line:84%
and that's really
what was occurring.

00:33:30.190 --> 00:33:33.120 align:middle line:90%


00:33:33.120 --> 00:33:38.020 align:middle line:84%
So I formed Acoustic
Brain Research in 1983

00:33:38.020 --> 00:33:40.260 align:middle line:84%
to scientifically
look at how music

00:33:40.260 --> 00:33:42.380 align:middle line:90%
and sound affect the brain.

00:33:42.380 --> 00:33:45.360 align:middle line:84%
And this was a loose
collection of researchers

00:33:45.360 --> 00:33:47.860 align:middle line:84%
all over the country--
universities,

00:33:47.860 --> 00:33:50.570 align:middle line:84%
independent labs--
looking at sound patterns

00:33:50.570 --> 00:33:52.400 align:middle line:84%
that I would compose,
and look at how

00:33:52.400 --> 00:33:55.500 align:middle line:84%
it would affect the brain,
mostly through EEG studies.

00:33:55.500 --> 00:33:57.710 align:middle line:84%
So I started writing
music for my clients

00:33:57.710 --> 00:34:00.710 align:middle line:84%
to accelerate
therapy, and to reach

00:34:00.710 --> 00:34:02.940 align:middle line:90%
deeper states of consciousness.

00:34:02.940 --> 00:34:05.990 align:middle line:84%
Most of us have one
part of the brain that

00:34:05.990 --> 00:34:07.870 align:middle line:84%
is more dominant than
the other in terms

00:34:07.870 --> 00:34:09.929 align:middle line:90%
of filtering the experience.

00:34:09.929 --> 00:34:12.810 align:middle line:84%
And for some people,
that's the left.

00:34:12.810 --> 00:34:16.150 align:middle line:84%
And that's the logical,
sequential side.

00:34:16.150 --> 00:34:18.750 align:middle line:84%
Then the other side of the
brain-- the right hemisphere--

00:34:18.750 --> 00:34:20.570 align:middle line:90%
is spatial intelligence.

00:34:20.570 --> 00:34:23.980 align:middle line:84%
It's actually very
happy with paradox,

00:34:23.980 --> 00:34:26.590 align:middle line:84%
and it's comfortable where
two things that are opposite

00:34:26.590 --> 00:34:27.960 align:middle line:90%
exist simultaneously.

00:34:27.960 --> 00:34:30.199 align:middle line:90%
The left brain can't stand that.

00:34:30.199 --> 00:34:32.960 align:middle line:84%
And the brain research shows
that when you are experiencing

00:34:32.960 --> 00:34:36.120 align:middle line:84%
pure sound without language,
the right side of the brain

00:34:36.120 --> 00:34:37.870 align:middle line:90%
lights up like a Christmas tree.

00:34:37.870 --> 00:34:41.920 align:middle line:84%
And all types of phenomena
occur in the right hemisphere

00:34:41.920 --> 00:34:43.714 align:middle line:84%
that do not occur over here
in the left hemisphere.

00:34:43.714 --> 00:34:46.219 align:middle line:90%


00:34:46.219 --> 00:34:48.030 align:middle line:84%
So let's start with
a sound meditation

00:34:48.030 --> 00:34:51.440 align:middle line:84%
to bring us all
to the same space.

00:34:51.440 --> 00:34:53.526 align:middle line:84%
When your mind wanders,
simply bring it back.

00:34:53.526 --> 00:34:59.974 align:middle line:90%


00:34:59.974 --> 00:42:13.210 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING AND CHANTING]

00:42:13.210 --> 00:42:14.950 align:middle line:84%
The ability to go
into a mystical state

00:42:14.950 --> 00:42:17.940 align:middle line:84%
of consciousness or receptive
creative state of consciousness

00:42:17.940 --> 00:42:20.120 align:middle line:90%
is a brain skill.

00:42:20.120 --> 00:42:21.630 align:middle line:90%
It's like typing.

00:42:21.630 --> 00:42:23.540 align:middle line:90%
Learning to ride a bike.

00:42:23.540 --> 00:42:24.797 align:middle line:90%
Anybody can learn it.

00:42:24.797 --> 00:42:28.773 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:42:28.773 --> 00:43:10.100 align:middle line:90%


00:43:10.100 --> 00:43:11.840 align:middle line:84%
Every human being
has that capacity,

00:43:11.840 --> 00:43:13.130 align:middle line:84%
and every human
being who has a voice

00:43:13.130 --> 00:43:16.570 align:middle line:84%
has the capacity to use that
voice to heal themselves

00:43:16.570 --> 00:43:18.090 align:middle line:90%
and another person.

00:43:18.090 --> 00:43:22.070 align:middle line:84%
Not even in something
external like sound healing,

00:43:22.070 --> 00:43:23.830 align:middle line:84%
but in how we speak
to each other.

00:43:23.830 --> 00:43:25.120 align:middle line:90%
The words we choose.

00:43:25.120 --> 00:43:26.800 align:middle line:90%
The tonality that we choose.

00:43:26.800 --> 00:43:30.620 align:middle line:84%
And we're creating the world
by how we speak to each other.

00:43:30.620 --> 00:43:46.790 align:middle line:90%


00:43:46.790 --> 00:43:49.965 align:middle line:84%
And then I had an encounter that
was totally unexpected, and out

00:43:49.965 --> 00:43:52.360 align:middle line:84%
of the blue, and
uninvited with a group

00:43:52.360 --> 00:43:55.475 align:middle line:90%
of beings called the Hathors.

00:43:55.475 --> 00:43:57.880 align:middle line:10%
I'd worked in brain
research for about 13 years

00:43:57.880 --> 00:44:00.370 align:middle line:10%
before I encountered
the Hathors,

00:44:00.370 --> 00:44:02.850 align:middle line:10%
so I had some understanding
of how sound and music affect

00:44:02.850 --> 00:44:05.340 align:middle line:10%
the braih-- that was my focus.

00:44:05.340 --> 00:44:07.790 align:middle line:84%
And I had, I thought, some
idea of what reality was,

00:44:07.790 --> 00:44:09.750 align:middle line:84%
and altered states of
consciousness-- that's

00:44:09.750 --> 00:44:11.540 align:middle line:90%
the field that I worked in.

00:44:11.540 --> 00:44:14.360 align:middle line:84%
And so then these beings showed
up in a meditation retreat--

00:44:14.360 --> 00:44:17.960 align:middle line:84%
I was doing a Siddha Yoga
retreat-- silent, by myself,

00:44:17.960 --> 00:44:19.650 align:middle line:90%
nobody else around.

00:44:19.650 --> 00:44:22.280 align:middle line:84%
And so they said they came
from another universe,

00:44:22.280 --> 00:44:26.090 align:middle line:84%
and so my mind was,
like, this is insanity.

00:44:26.090 --> 00:44:29.120 align:middle line:84%
So I was having these psychic
experiences with the Hathors

00:44:29.120 --> 00:44:32.380 align:middle line:84%
and hearing psychic
communications.

00:44:32.380 --> 00:44:34.840 align:middle line:10%
I see them as a
mental impression.

00:44:34.840 --> 00:44:38.780 align:middle line:10%
One is observing, and there's
one that speaks, and he says,

00:44:38.780 --> 00:44:41.515 align:middle line:10%
we are the Hathors,
and we come with love,

00:44:41.515 --> 00:44:44.340 align:middle line:10%
and the sounding of a new
reality for your Earth.

00:44:44.340 --> 00:44:46.651 align:middle line:90%


00:44:46.651 --> 00:44:47.350 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:44:47.350 --> 00:44:51.840 align:middle line:90%


00:44:51.840 --> 00:44:54.945 align:middle line:90%
Now, where are you from?

00:44:54.945 --> 00:44:56.620 align:middle line:90%
We're from Venus.

00:44:56.620 --> 00:44:57.670 align:middle line:90%
Great.

00:44:57.670 --> 00:45:00.760 align:middle line:90%
Just fucking great.

00:45:00.760 --> 00:45:04.300 align:middle line:84%
I'm talking to an imaginary
beings who are from Venus.

00:45:04.300 --> 00:45:07.550 align:middle line:84%
So I was convinced that
this was a delusion.

00:45:07.550 --> 00:45:09.611 align:middle line:84%
I was a practicing
psychotherapist

00:45:09.611 --> 00:45:10.310 align:middle line:90%
in North Carolina.

00:45:10.310 --> 00:45:14.520 align:middle line:84%
I had PhD supervisors,
and I had my niche.

00:45:14.520 --> 00:45:17.650 align:middle line:84%
And so then I had to think of
them-- OK, they're archetypes.

00:45:17.650 --> 00:45:19.600 align:middle line:90%
I went to my Jungian training.

00:45:19.600 --> 00:45:22.110 align:middle line:84%
They're simply archetypes,
so they're not real.

00:45:22.110 --> 00:45:23.310 align:middle line:84%
They claim they're
real, but they're

00:45:23.310 --> 00:45:26.970 align:middle line:84%
not really real, you know,
they're aspects of the mind.

00:45:26.970 --> 00:45:29.960 align:middle line:84%
Creative, resourceful,
yes, but not real.

00:45:29.960 --> 00:45:31.360 align:middle line:84%
Thank you, I've
got them in a box.

00:45:31.360 --> 00:45:33.130 align:middle line:90%
I'm comfortable with it.

00:45:33.130 --> 00:45:37.540 align:middle line:84%
So nobody knew about
this part of my life.

00:45:37.540 --> 00:45:39.830 align:middle line:90%
So I never peeped a word.

00:45:39.830 --> 00:45:44.430 align:middle line:84%
And then they said, we'd
like you to write a book.

00:45:44.430 --> 00:45:46.240 align:middle line:90%
I said, yeah, right.

00:45:46.240 --> 00:45:50.760 align:middle line:10%
I'm going to put my hard earned
credentials-- my sacred letters

00:45:50.760 --> 00:45:55.370 align:middle line:10%
that go after my name--
on a book about weirdos

00:45:55.370 --> 00:45:58.820 align:middle line:10%
from another universe
that live on Venus,

00:45:58.820 --> 00:46:02.960 align:middle line:10%
and came through Sirius to
come in and help balance

00:46:02.960 --> 00:46:04.920 align:middle line:10%
this universe for this time.

00:46:04.920 --> 00:46:06.430 align:middle line:10%
Yeah, right.

00:46:06.430 --> 00:46:09.846 align:middle line:10%
[SINGING AND CHANTING]

00:46:09.846 --> 00:46:20.110 align:middle line:90%


00:46:20.110 --> 00:46:23.020 align:middle line:10%
And they gave me some
information about geometry

00:46:23.020 --> 00:46:25.910 align:middle line:10%
in the brain-- information
that I didn't know,

00:46:25.910 --> 00:46:27.891 align:middle line:10%
but I recognized as significant.

00:46:27.891 --> 00:46:29.290 align:middle line:84%
Because they were
talking about the brain,

00:46:29.290 --> 00:46:31.000 align:middle line:84%
and the geometry
of consciousness,

00:46:31.000 --> 00:46:32.970 align:middle line:84%
and relationship to
sound and emotion.

00:46:32.970 --> 00:46:35.990 align:middle line:10%
And I found all this
stuff very intriguing.

00:46:35.990 --> 00:46:38.590 align:middle line:84%
And said, if I taught
this to some people,

00:46:38.590 --> 00:46:42.010 align:middle line:84%
I would observe rapid change--
improvement-- in brain

00:46:42.010 --> 00:46:43.830 align:middle line:90%
function and creativity.

00:46:43.830 --> 00:46:47.400 align:middle line:84%
And I did tests--
three beta test sites--

00:46:47.400 --> 00:46:49.500 align:middle line:84%
and by god, that's
exactly what happened.

00:46:49.500 --> 00:46:50.810 align:middle line:90%
It was amazing.

00:46:50.810 --> 00:46:52.880 align:middle line:84%
So I had to acknowledge
this information, although I

00:46:52.880 --> 00:46:54.630 align:middle line:84%
couldn't buy that
it came from who

00:46:54.630 --> 00:46:58.640 align:middle line:84%
they said they were, because it
was too outside the box for me.

00:46:58.640 --> 00:47:00.910 align:middle line:90%
But the information is valid.

00:47:00.910 --> 00:47:04.420 align:middle line:84%
And then I was in
California doing a workshop

00:47:04.420 --> 00:47:06.490 align:middle line:84%
with the Hathors, and they
were starting to tone--

00:47:06.490 --> 00:47:08.740 align:middle line:84%
they were having me tone-- and
they would bring these sounds

00:47:08.740 --> 00:47:10.510 align:middle line:84%
through, and that's
what really opened

00:47:10.510 --> 00:47:13.324 align:middle line:90%
up the sound work as it is now.

00:47:13.324 --> 00:47:20.080 align:middle line:90%
[GONG]

00:47:20.080 --> 00:47:23.959 align:middle line:90%
[GONG]

00:47:23.959 --> 00:47:27.780 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING AND CHANTING]

00:47:27.780 --> 00:47:30.380 align:middle line:84%
I've become like a tuning
fork to the information

00:47:30.380 --> 00:47:31.990 align:middle line:90%
that is coming to me.

00:47:31.990 --> 00:47:35.190 align:middle line:84%
In shamanism, they call it being
the hollow reed, so what I do

00:47:35.190 --> 00:47:37.840 align:middle line:90%
is to step out of the way.

00:47:37.840 --> 00:47:39.630 align:middle line:84%
And in terms of
brain frequencies,

00:47:39.630 --> 00:47:41.210 align:middle line:84%
I would say I go
into an alpha state,

00:47:41.210 --> 00:47:43.480 align:middle line:84%
and in that state of
alpha, I can attend

00:47:43.480 --> 00:47:46.630 align:middle line:84%
to what I need to do
vocally, but for that moment,

00:47:46.630 --> 00:47:49.534 align:middle line:84%
I surrender my
voice to the energy.

00:47:49.534 --> 00:47:52.908 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING AND CHANTING]

00:47:52.908 --> 00:48:07.500 align:middle line:90%


00:48:07.500 --> 00:48:09.450 align:middle line:84%
When I started working
shamanically with the drums,

00:48:09.450 --> 00:48:11.770 align:middle line:84%
then the whole shamanic
world opened up. d

00:48:11.770 --> 00:48:15.600 align:middle line:84%
And the animal spirits can come
through my voice, and shamans,

00:48:15.600 --> 00:48:18.870 align:middle line:84%
and beings from
other traditions.

00:48:18.870 --> 00:48:20.720 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes I'll
just look over here

00:48:20.720 --> 00:48:24.110 align:middle line:84%
and I'll see 12, 13 shamans
all with their drums.

00:48:24.110 --> 00:48:27.380 align:middle line:84%
Or there'll be 108 lamas when
I'm in the Tibetan tradition.

00:48:27.380 --> 00:48:28.960 align:middle line:84%
I feel like sometimes
I'm like a doorway.

00:48:28.960 --> 00:48:30.150 align:middle line:90%
I just open the door.

00:48:30.150 --> 00:48:33.005 align:middle line:84%
Or I'm a chauffeur, and I
look in the backseat to see

00:48:33.005 --> 00:48:35.318 align:middle line:90%
who I'm driving at the moment.

00:48:35.318 --> 00:48:39.190 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING AND CHANTING]

00:48:39.190 --> 00:49:58.767 align:middle line:90%


00:49:58.767 --> 00:50:00.100 align:middle line:10%
INTERVIEWER: What do
you say to people--

00:50:00.100 --> 00:50:01.320 align:middle line:10%
or maybe you don't
say to people--

00:50:01.320 --> 00:50:03.260 align:middle line:10%
that think this is just nuts.

00:50:03.260 --> 00:50:04.480 align:middle line:10%
I mean, you must--

00:50:04.480 --> 00:50:06.930 align:middle line:10%
I agree with them.

00:50:06.930 --> 00:50:11.030 align:middle line:84%
And I move in two
diametrically opposed worlds.

00:50:11.030 --> 00:50:12.450 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:50:12.450 --> 00:50:16.690 align:middle line:84%
I think of myself as a
brain researcher, a musician,

00:50:16.690 --> 00:50:19.190 align:middle line:84%
I'm logical in how
I look at things.

00:50:19.190 --> 00:50:22.800 align:middle line:84%
So I'm fascinated with neurology
and what goes on in the brain,

00:50:22.800 --> 00:50:25.990 align:middle line:84%
and there's this
other side that is,

00:50:25.990 --> 00:50:28.670 align:middle line:84%
well, I call it off the
charts into woo woo land.

00:50:28.670 --> 00:50:33.208 align:middle line:84%
And so, for me, a
lot of stuff is nuts.

