with other teachers.

01:04:32.390 --> 01:04:36.490 align:middle line:10%
Japsang was the most
incredible encounter that I've

01:04:36.490 --> 01:04:38.940 align:middle line:10%
had in Tibetan Buddhism,
and I've had some pretty

01:04:38.940 --> 01:04:40.420 align:middle line:10%
extraordinary encounters.

01:04:40.420 --> 01:04:42.880 align:middle line:90%
He was a peer.

01:04:42.880 --> 01:04:48.540 align:middle line:84%
He was a guru in the
sense of the true guru.

01:04:48.540 --> 01:04:52.160 align:middle line:84%
Truest guru is the one
that resides in each of us,

01:04:52.160 --> 01:04:56.220 align:middle line:84%
but a true guru is someone who
is a bridge between the worlds,

01:04:56.220 --> 01:04:59.910 align:middle line:84%
and he can move back and
forth between the worlds.

01:04:59.910 --> 01:05:04.070 align:middle line:84%
And so I can go to him,
and ask him questions,

01:05:04.070 --> 01:05:08.260 align:middle line:84%
and he refines
various understandings

01:05:08.260 --> 01:05:09.405 align:middle line:90%
I have from his perspective.

01:05:09.405 --> 01:05:16.141 align:middle line:90%


01:05:16.141 --> 01:05:20.117 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING AND CHANTING]

01:05:20.117 --> 01:05:47.310 align:middle line:90%


01:05:47.310 --> 01:05:52.380 align:middle line:84%
The nuns in Tibet are
an extraordinary force.

01:05:52.380 --> 01:05:55.920 align:middle line:84%
I had no knowledge that nuns
chanted the way they chant,

01:05:55.920 --> 01:05:58.440 align:middle line:84%
and so I remember going to
the Gyantse Nunnery, which

01:05:58.440 --> 01:06:04.010 align:middle line:84%
is very remote, and hearing them
sing, and it was like this--

01:06:04.010 --> 01:06:05.440 align:middle line:90%
I was drunk.

01:06:05.440 --> 01:06:08.732 align:middle line:84%
I was drunk on the chants
coming out of these nuns.

01:06:08.732 --> 01:06:13.214 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

01:06:13.214 --> 01:06:54.600 align:middle line:90%


01:06:54.600 --> 01:06:55.767 align:middle line:84%
And these are the
nuns of Gyantse.

01:06:55.767 --> 01:06:57.099 align:middle line:84%
These are the ones
that we're recording.

01:06:57.099 --> 01:06:57.860 align:middle line:90%
These are Gyantse.

01:06:57.860 --> 01:06:58.560 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

01:06:58.560 --> 01:07:01.660 align:middle line:84%
And certain ones we've used,
like, for the CD and stuff,

01:07:01.660 --> 01:07:03.961 align:middle line:84%
like, you're familiar
with this, for instance.

01:07:03.961 --> 01:07:07.420 align:middle line:84%
Right.
It hit me like a ton of bricks.

01:07:07.420 --> 01:07:10.390 align:middle line:84%
In this world of
imbalance, nobody

01:07:10.390 --> 01:07:13.370 align:middle line:84%
had ever bothered to record
the voices of the women.

01:07:13.370 --> 01:07:16.520 align:middle line:90%
Nobody knew the nuns chanted.

01:07:16.520 --> 01:07:20.010 align:middle line:10%
Because of that work that
Judy envisioned, and the CD was

01:07:20.010 --> 01:07:22.980 align:middle line:10%
created, and all the
profits go back to the nuns,

01:07:22.980 --> 01:07:27.280 align:middle line:10%
they were able to repair a
wall that was a huge gap,

01:07:27.280 --> 01:07:30.010 align:middle line:10%
and expand the nunnery--
make it much larger.

01:07:30.010 --> 01:07:32.980 align:middle line:84%
They provided winter
robes for all the nuns,

01:07:32.980 --> 01:07:35.910 align:middle line:90%
because they were threadbare.

01:07:35.910 --> 01:07:39.560 align:middle line:84%
And two nuns could be
sent to medical school.

01:07:39.560 --> 01:07:42.280 align:middle line:84%
And that came out of
this vision that Judy

01:07:42.280 --> 01:07:44.500 align:middle line:84%
had to empower the
nuns, and that also it's

01:07:44.500 --> 01:07:46.430 align:middle line:84%
a beautiful expression
of the feminine,

01:07:46.430 --> 01:07:48.016 align:middle line:84%
because the feminine
is about relationship.

01:07:48.016 --> 01:07:53.812 align:middle line:90%


01:07:53.812 --> 01:07:55.270 align:middle line:84%
Well, the first
time the feminine

01:07:55.270 --> 01:08:00.570 align:middle line:84%
showed up for me as a reference
point was after my episode

01:08:00.570 --> 01:08:04.630 align:middle line:84%
when I was 18 in
my uncle's pasture.

01:08:04.630 --> 01:08:08.740 align:middle line:84%
I went into the Western
mystical contemplative tradition

01:08:08.740 --> 01:08:12.650 align:middle line:84%
very deeply, so I had these
many numinous experiences

01:08:12.650 --> 01:08:17.240 align:middle line:90%
with Mary, mother of Jesus.

01:08:17.240 --> 01:08:22.430 align:middle line:84%
So my personal journey was, as
I went deeper into mysticism--

01:08:22.430 --> 01:08:25.490 align:middle line:84%
the Christian contemplative
tradition-- there was

01:08:25.490 --> 01:08:26.930 align:middle line:84%
a place where there
was kind of a dead end,

01:08:26.930 --> 01:08:29.490 align:middle line:84%
because it did not explain
my experience that I

01:08:29.490 --> 01:08:32.430 align:middle line:84%
had when I was 18-- that
mystical experience.

01:08:32.430 --> 01:08:34.340 align:middle line:84%
So it took me into
the East, and there I

01:08:34.340 --> 01:08:37.810 align:middle line:84%
met these feminine
archetypes, these goddesses

01:08:37.810 --> 01:08:40.109 align:middle line:84%
in other traditions,
like Parvati,

01:08:40.109 --> 01:08:42.310 align:middle line:84%
[INAUDIBLE] of
Shiva and Saraswati,

01:08:42.310 --> 01:08:47.109 align:middle line:84%
and Lakshmi, and Kuan Yin,
and all these goddesses.

01:08:47.109 --> 01:08:50.990 align:middle line:84%
And I formed relationships
with them through meditation.

01:08:50.990 --> 01:08:53.779 align:middle line:84%
And my bhakti for
these goddesses

01:08:53.779 --> 01:08:55.690 align:middle line:84%
was so immense that when
I was in their presence,

01:08:55.690 --> 01:08:59.050 align:middle line:84%
I would be elevated, and then
I look at women on the Earth.

01:08:59.050 --> 01:09:03.380 align:middle line:84%
And in India, still to this
day, if the husband dies,

01:09:03.380 --> 01:09:05.830 align:middle line:84%
sometimes the woman is supposed
to-- in certain castes-- is

01:09:05.830 --> 01:09:07.270 align:middle line:84%
supposed to jump onto
the funeral pyre,

01:09:07.270 --> 01:09:10.029 align:middle line:84%
because she has no life
left when the husband dies.

01:09:10.029 --> 01:09:13.000 align:middle line:84%
And there are women that are
given clitorectomies in Africa.

01:09:13.000 --> 01:09:17.800 align:middle line:84%
So these horrendous things
are taking place in this world

01:09:17.800 --> 01:09:19.270 align:middle line:90%
against the feminine.

01:09:19.270 --> 01:09:24.510 align:middle line:84%
So as I began to look
at all this stuff--

01:09:24.510 --> 01:09:26.939 align:middle line:84%
the political, social,
the neurological,

01:09:26.939 --> 01:09:30.439 align:middle line:84%
and the spiritual
disempowerment of women,

01:09:30.439 --> 01:09:33.649 align:middle line:84%
and my place as a man in
the midst of all that--

01:09:33.649 --> 01:09:35.189 align:middle line:84%
how do I come to
terms with that?

01:09:35.189 --> 01:09:37.710 align:middle line:90%


01:09:37.710 --> 01:09:39.300 align:middle line:84%
The pivotal point
for me that pulled

01:09:39.300 --> 01:09:42.920 align:middle line:84%
all of these different things
together into one gestalt

01:09:42.920 --> 01:09:44.160 align:middle line:90%
was when I met Judi Sion.

01:09:44.160 --> 01:09:47.859 align:middle line:90%


01:09:47.859 --> 01:09:51.800 align:middle line:84%
I called, and I sounded like
somebody calling John Lennon.

01:09:51.800 --> 01:09:53.510 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know he sang.

01:09:53.510 --> 01:09:55.410 align:middle line:84%
I knew he was some
sort of a teacher.

01:09:55.410 --> 01:09:57.350 align:middle line:84%
And I called, and I left
a message, and I said,

01:09:57.350 --> 01:10:00.980 align:middle line:84%
I have an amazing friend, and
I need to find the most amazing

01:10:00.980 --> 01:10:06.450 align:middle line:84%
present, and I'm wondering
if you could be the Christmas

01:10:06.450 --> 01:10:08.780 align:middle line:90%
present for my friend.

01:10:08.780 --> 01:10:11.160 align:middle line:84%
And it hadn't been--
and I hung up the phone,

01:10:11.160 --> 01:10:13.840 align:middle line:84%
and thought, oh
my god, you fool.

01:10:13.840 --> 01:10:16.080 align:middle line:90%
And Tom called back.

01:10:16.080 --> 01:10:19.501 align:middle line:10%
So we went up to where Tom
was living at the time.

01:10:19.501 --> 01:10:20.680 align:middle line:84%
Hello.
How are you?

01:10:20.680 --> 01:10:21.420 align:middle line:90%
Fine and dandy.

01:10:21.420 --> 01:10:24.895 align:middle line:84%
And he unzips this suitcase, and
brings out this crystal bowl,

01:10:24.895 --> 01:10:27.480 align:middle line:84%
and I was like, huh,
I wonder what that is?

01:10:27.480 --> 01:10:29.310 align:middle line:84%
I wonder what he's going
to do with that thing?

01:10:29.310 --> 01:10:35.570 align:middle line:84%
And he started making sound,
and I went to another dimension.

01:10:35.570 --> 01:10:39.760 align:middle line:84%
That was the first time my
consciousness-- my brain

01:10:39.760 --> 01:10:42.032 align:middle line:84%
state-- had been
altered by sound.

01:10:42.032 --> 01:10:45.984 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING AND SINGING]

01:10:45.984 --> 01:10:56.150 align:middle line:90%


01:10:56.150 --> 01:10:58.500 align:middle line:84%
And Tom said, I just
need to tell you,

01:10:58.500 --> 01:11:00.865 align:middle line:84%
I don't, I don't,
I don't do this.

01:11:00.865 --> 01:11:02.570 align:middle line:90%
I said, you don't do what?

01:11:02.570 --> 01:11:06.010 align:middle line:84%
He said, I don't see
people in my home.

01:11:06.010 --> 01:11:07.910 align:middle line:90%
I don't do private sessions.

01:11:07.910 --> 01:11:10.480 align:middle line:84%
I was like, my first
thought was, well, then,

01:11:10.480 --> 01:11:12.220 align:middle line:90%
why did you do this?

01:11:12.220 --> 01:11:14.590 align:middle line:90%
And said that, being me.

01:11:14.590 --> 01:11:16.010 align:middle line:90%
Why am I here?

01:11:16.010 --> 01:11:16.900 align:middle line:90%
Why did you do this?

01:11:16.900 --> 01:11:18.940 align:middle line:84%
He said, because the
Hathors told me to.

01:11:18.940 --> 01:11:27.570 align:middle line:90%


01:11:27.570 --> 01:11:29.570 align:middle line:84%
There's a place on Route
1 where the Nottoway

01:11:29.570 --> 01:11:31.940 align:middle line:90%
River crosses Route 1.

01:11:31.940 --> 01:11:35.230 align:middle line:84%
And that was a bridge, I'm told,
that my birth father worked on,

01:11:35.230 --> 01:11:38.280 align:middle line:84%
and that's where
he met my mother.

01:11:38.280 --> 01:11:41.470 align:middle line:84%
We were on our way
to visit relatives.

01:11:41.470 --> 01:11:42.870 align:middle line:84%
TOM KENYON: We lived
in Norfolk, Virginia,

01:11:42.870 --> 01:11:44.420 align:middle line:84%
and my grandmother
and grandfather lived

01:11:44.420 --> 01:11:45.590 align:middle line:90%
in Greensboro, North Carolina.

01:11:45.590 --> 01:11:50.110 align:middle line:84%
So my mother, and I, and
my brother were on the bus.

01:11:50.110 --> 01:11:51.380 align:middle line:84%
JUDI SION: So I was
in the backseat,

01:11:51.380 --> 01:11:54.500 align:middle line:84%
and I just remember this--
coming alongside a bus,

01:11:54.500 --> 01:11:56.330 align:middle line:90%
and just looking over.

01:11:56.330 --> 01:11:58.490 align:middle line:84%
There was a little
boy in the window.

01:11:58.490 --> 01:12:00.860 align:middle line:84%
TOM KENYON: And I'm
sitting by the big window,

01:12:00.860 --> 01:12:02.850 align:middle line:90%
and I look down at a car.

01:12:02.850 --> 01:12:04.190 align:middle line:90%
JUDI SION: And our eyes locked.

01:12:04.190 --> 01:12:08.320 align:middle line:84%
And the cars moved at what
I call, flying formation.

01:12:08.320 --> 01:12:09.640 align:middle line:84%
It could have been
for five seconds.

01:12:09.640 --> 01:12:11.290 align:middle line:84%
It could have been
for five minutes.

01:12:11.290 --> 01:12:12.310 align:middle line:90%
It seemed forever.

01:12:12.310 --> 01:12:13.810 align:middle line:84%
TOM KENYON: And so we're
just hovering there,

01:12:13.810 --> 01:12:17.150 align:middle line:84%
and I looked down and there's
this girl who's about my age,

01:12:17.150 --> 01:12:19.190 align:middle line:90%
and it was like, oh, hello.

01:12:19.190 --> 01:12:20.740 align:middle line:84%
JUDI SION: Deep
in his eyes, there

01:12:20.740 --> 01:12:23.250 align:middle line:84%
was something-- I knew
that little boy was

01:12:23.250 --> 01:12:25.220 align:middle line:84%
going to play guitar, and
I knew that little boy

01:12:25.220 --> 01:12:26.160 align:middle line:90%
was going to sing.

01:12:26.160 --> 01:12:28.710 align:middle line:84%
TOM KENYON: And then
the car passes the bus.

01:12:28.710 --> 01:12:32.290 align:middle line:84%
And so I happened to write
about it when I was writing

01:12:32.290 --> 01:12:34.420 align:middle line:84%
my story for The
Magdalen Manuscript,

01:12:34.420 --> 01:12:37.660 align:middle line:84%
because it struck my heart
at such a deep level.

01:12:37.660 --> 01:12:41.990 align:middle line:84%
But what happened was that,
when Tom read my story,

01:12:41.990 --> 01:12:43.360 align:middle line:90%
he said, wow.

01:12:43.360 --> 01:12:45.930 align:middle line:84%
That same thing happened to
me when I was a little boy.

01:12:45.930 --> 01:12:48.560 align:middle line:84%
I said, yeah, but I know
exactly where I was.

01:12:48.560 --> 01:12:50.266 align:middle line:84%
I know where I
was, on what road.

01:12:50.266 --> 01:12:54.686 align:middle line:84%
He said, so do I. And we
matched it up, and we thought,

01:12:54.686 --> 01:12:55.385 align:middle line:90%
could this be?

01:12:55.385 --> 01:13:06.143 align:middle line:90%


01:13:06.143 --> 01:13:09.070 align:middle line:84%
Although the Hathors
are androgynous beings,

01:13:09.070 --> 01:13:11.320 align:middle line:84%
meaning balanced
between male and female,

01:13:11.320 --> 01:13:13.850 align:middle line:84%
how they view our
current situation

01:13:13.850 --> 01:13:16.340 align:middle line:84%
is that it is time that
the feminine nature has

01:13:16.340 --> 01:13:20.540 align:middle line:84%
to rise up in balance to the
masculine in its expression

01:13:20.540 --> 01:13:22.940 align:middle line:90%
here on Earth.

01:13:22.940 --> 01:13:27.320 align:middle line:84%
Earth is held
symbolically as feminine.

01:13:27.320 --> 01:13:29.120 align:middle line:90%
We even call it Mother Earth.

01:13:29.120 --> 01:13:34.500 align:middle line:84%
So the feminine is degredated
and is held in lower esteem

01:13:34.500 --> 01:13:36.760 align:middle line:84%
in many of our
spiritual traditions,

01:13:36.760 --> 01:13:40.450 align:middle line:84%
because we have such
disregard for the Earth

01:13:40.450 --> 01:13:41.790 align:middle line:90%
itself, and the feminine.

01:13:41.790 --> 01:13:44.270 align:middle line:90%


01:13:44.270 --> 01:13:46.580 align:middle line:84%
So one of the
myths in society is

01:13:46.580 --> 01:13:50.200 align:middle line:84%
that here-- everybody
here-- I don't sense

01:13:50.200 --> 01:13:52.760 align:middle line:90%
any virgin births in this room.

01:13:52.760 --> 01:13:55.750 align:middle line:84%
So all of us got
here through sex.

01:13:55.750 --> 01:14:00.310 align:middle line:84%
A mother and father had coitus,
and there was a big bang,

01:14:00.310 --> 01:14:07.240 align:middle line:84%
and our culture says that it
was a mad rush of the sperm

01:14:07.240 --> 01:14:11.760 align:middle line:84%
to get to the egg, and the
first sperm to get to the egg

01:14:11.760 --> 01:14:13.790 align:middle line:90%
was the winner.

01:14:13.790 --> 01:14:17.090 align:middle line:84%
And that's a very
patriarchal, masculine view.

01:14:17.090 --> 01:14:20.800 align:middle line:84%
But genetics is now discovering
that it's not quite true.

01:14:20.800 --> 01:14:28.860 align:middle line:84%
That the egg actually senses
the approaching horde,

01:14:28.860 --> 01:14:31.410 align:middle line:84%
sends out tentacles
of information,

01:14:31.410 --> 01:14:35.110 align:middle line:84%
and scans them
before they arrive.

